<h2>What will happen if I don’t pay the outstanding service charges?</h2>
<p>
Failure to make payment or contact us by <%= @return_date_lba %> will result in legal action being taken in the County Court without further notice.
</p>

<p>
Should legal action be necessary, any increase to the arrears stated above will be added. All court costs, including the Council’s, and legal fees will also be added, which could increase the sum owed by up to 8%.
</p>

<p>
If you choose to ignore any court order judgement and you still have not paid the arrears, we will have no option but to take further action against you. This would include issuing further and stronger legal proceedings that may result in you losing your home. Where applicable, we will contact your mortgage lender to advise them of our intentions to pursue recovery of this debt.
</p>

<h2>How can I make payment?</h2>
<p>
To pay by debit or credit card over the phone please call 020 8356 2299 between 9am and  5pm Monday to Friday. Alternatively, cheques should be made payable to ‘London Borough of Hackney’. Further details of these payment options are enclosed.
</p>

<h2>What will happen if I pay late?</h2>
<p>
Should you make payment after the 30 days have elapsed but before a claim is sent for issuing to court, you should contact the Council immediately or you may still be at risk for court costs. Similarly, paying after a claim has been submitted for issuing to court will result in you being liable for interest and costs.
</p>

<p>
If you have any queries regarding this matter please contact <strong><%= @username %> on 020 8356 2299.</strong>
